{
  "texts": [
    "The use of LLMs by insurance companies for claim processing and fraud detection raises significant ethical concerns 37.",
    "Currently, several LLMs, including versions of the ChatGPT family, are employed by both EHR systems and insurance companies [38] [39] [40], creating a conflict of interest when similar datasets are used by entities with opposing objectives 21, 41.",
    "For example, insurance companies use LLMs to minimize costs by detecting fraud and reducing claim payouts 18, while medical institutions use them to optimize billing and maximize reimbursements.",
    "This dual use of LLMs can lead to biased outcomes, where patient care decisions are influenced more by financial considerations than medical necessity.",
    "Consequently, legitimate claims may be unfairly denied, underscoring the need for careful oversight of LLM use in these contexts."
  ]
}